%% Diagram: DNS resolution flow (high-level)
%% Type: sequenceDiagram
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as Application
    participant Stub as Stub resolver (OS)
    participant Rec as Recursive resolver (cache)
    participant Root as Root server
    participant TLD as TLD server (.com)
    participant Auth as Authoritative server

    App->>Stub: getaddrinfo("www.example.com")
    Stub->>Rec: Query A www.example.com (RD=1)
    alt Cache hit
        Rec-->>Stub: Cached answer (TTL remaining)
    else Cache miss
        Rec->>Root: Query .com NS
        Root-->>Rec: Referral + glue
        Rec->>TLD: Query example.com NS
        TLD-->>Rec: Referral + glue
        Rec->>Auth: Query A www.example.com
        Auth-->>Rec: A record (TTL=N)
        Rec-->>Stub: Answer (caches each step per its TTL)
    end
    Stub-->>App: IP address(es)
